    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oversized chalices, bowls, or urns used for collecting ballots by a papal conclave, monastic election, or other religious institutions' election, typically when choosing a leader.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
